## M20i.1: cloning a loop-borrow alias is rejected.
##
## `for cb in ?subs` binds `cb` as a borrowed view of the Vec
## slot. `+cb` (clone) would bump the strong refcount on the
## borrowed handle and silently smuggle a new strong reference
## past the loop boundary. Per GPT-5.5's M20i.1 design pass:
## clone-from-borrow has no V1 form — explicit clone-from-borrow
## semantics are deferred until the substrate decides between a
## dedicated primitive vs an opt-in `.clone()` method.
##
## The diagnostic fires twice (defense-in-depth): sema's type
## mismatch (push expects `*Closure()`, got `?*Closure()`) AND
## the ownership rejection on the loop-borrow alias.

sub main()
  count: *Cell(Int) = *Cell(value: 0)
  cb1: *Closure() = *Closure(|+count| count.set(count.get() + 1))

  subs: Vec(*Closure()) = Vec()
  (!subs).push(+cb1)

  other: Vec(*Closure()) = Vec()
  for cb in ?subs
    (!other).push(+cb)
